                    <msContents>
                        <summary> A treatise on internal medicine by <persName>Honma
                                Sōken</persName>, also known as Genchō, covering a number of Honma’s
                            medical and surgical practices in katakana-majiri script, with coloured
                            illustrations by an unknown artist. It was privately published by the
                            author in 1864. This copy is incomplete, lacking volume 14. </summary>

                        <textLang mainLang="ja" source="IANA">Japanese</textLang>

                        <msItem n="1" xml:id="Japanese_19">

                            <author key="person_76237324" source="VIAF">
                                <persName type="original" xml:lang="ja">本間棗軒</persName>
                                <persName type="standard" xml:lang="ja-Latn">Honma Sōken</persName>
                                <note> Honma Sōken (1804-1872) entered Hanaoka Seishū’s school of
                                    surgery in 1827 but left after a short while to spend two months
                                    studying in Nagasaki with Philipp Granz von Siebold (1796-1866),
                                    the doctor at Deshima who was later to achieve fame as a
                                    japanologist. Honma’s view was that Hanaoka Seishū’s surgical
                                    techniques were superior to Siebold’s.</note>
                            </author>

                            <title>
                                <title type="original" xml:lang="ja" source="IANA">内科秘録</title>
                                <title type="standard" xml:lang="ja-Latn" source="IANA">Naika
                                    hiroku</title>
                                <title type="standard" xml:lang="en" source="IANA">Secret treatise
                                    on internal medicine</title>
                            </title>

                            <filiation><p>See <ref target="https://kotenseki.nijl.ac.jp/?ln=en"
                                >Kotenseki Work ID: 390772</ref> for copies of <title>内科秘録</title> held
                                    by other institutions.</p>
                            </filiation>

                        </msItem>

